 <item> <title>Arkansas to Receive $5.3 Million to Continue Efforts to Turn Around its Lowest-Performing Schools</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/arkansas-receive-53-million-continue-efforts-turn-around-its-lowest-performing-schools</link>
 <description>Today, U.S. Secretary of Education Arne Duncan announced that Arkansas will receive $5.3 million to continue efforts to turn around its persistently lowest achieving schools through the Department&#039;s School Improvement Grant (SIG) program. Arkansas is one of 13 states that will receive SIG funding.</description>
