 <item> <title>Arkansas to Receive More Than $119 Million in Additional Recovery Funds</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/arkansas-receive-more-119-million-additional-recovery-funds</link>
 <description>U. S. Secretary of Education Arne Duncan today announced that an additional $119,807,496 is now available for Arkansas under the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act (ARRA) of 2009.  To date, Arkansas has received $779,540,450 through the Recovery Act. The state recently reported that recovery dollars have been used to provide funding for more than 600 education jobs from Oct. 1 to Dec.</description>
